content.description: From good holds down and left pull on and climb up the cool arete feature.  Take care on some of the holds and the spike on the arete.
content.protection: A few pads and maybe a spot.  Landing is not perfect and the topout is over another boulder.
content.location: 100 feet down and left of the big red slab there are some big boulders and this is in the middle of them.

content.description: From a sit, w/ your left hand in an undercling and your right on and edge, using the detached block for your feet move right to a gaston, then do a long pull through to better holds, then the top.
content.location: On the boulder below Scapularis facing downhill on the left side of the face.  Easy to approach from below, walk just past big red on the Tumbled Rocks trail, go up the hill where it looks reasonable in a little talus field.  After 100 feet traverse right (north) and it is a pretty and slighty overhannging face.

content.description: In the left edge of the boulder field.  Tick or be ticked?
